Polish shares close higher , seen extending gains . Polish shares rose after a three - session fall and analysts said strong buying in the continuous sessions after the price fixing signalled further growth . Analysts said , however , the market would still be under pressure from large privatisations , which might keep it locked in its over 2 . 5 - month long horizontal trend in the longer term . " The falls were strong enough to make investors use the situation for buying . . . at least the beginning of the next week should be good , " said Krzysztof Olszewski , an analyst at Bank Slaski brokerage . 
